<Link id="l00449" /><CodeLine lineNumber="449"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// select (cmp slt, X, Y), X, Y &lt;--&gt; select (not (not (cmp slt, X, Y))), X, Y</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A simple and fast domtree-based CSE pass.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This pass does a simple depth-first walk over the dominator tree,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><Highlight kind="comment">/// eliminating trivially redundant instructions and using instsimplify to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00638" /><CodeLine lineNumber="638"><Highlight kind="comment">/// canonicalize things as it goes. It is intended to be fast and catch obvious</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00639" /><CodeLine lineNumber="639"><Highlight kind="comment">/// cases so that instcombine and other passes are more effective. It is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00640" /><CodeLine lineNumber="640"><Highlight kind="comment">/// expected that a later pass of GVN will catch the interesting/hard cases.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00641" /><CodeLine lineNumber="641" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/#a25a26ce8b3780d7bf77dbec85d7e3f30">EarlyCSE</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00657" /><CodeLine lineNumber="657"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00658" /><CodeLine lineNumber="658"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// A scoped hash table of the current values of all of our simple</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00659" /><CodeLine lineNumber="659"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// scalar expressions.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00660" /><CodeLine lineNumber="660"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00661" /><CodeLine lineNumber="661"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// As we walk down the domtree, we look to see if instructions are in this:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00662" /><CodeLine lineNumber="662"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// if so, we replace them with what we find, otherwise we insert them so</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00663" /><CodeLine lineNumber="663"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// that dominated values can succeed in their lookup.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00664" /><CodeLine lineNumber="664" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/#a1fdc6655978cda56c76b557d6d4d81e7"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/#aba4b51f960b607643c1c0d4b3c103fd9">ScopedHTType</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/#a1fdc6655978cda56c76b557d6d4d81e7">AvailableValues</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00665" /><CodeLine lineNumber="665"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00666" /><CodeLine lineNumber="666"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// A scoped hash table of the current values of previously encountered</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00667" /><CodeLine lineNumber="667"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// memory locations.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00668" /><CodeLine lineNumber="668"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00669" /><CodeLine lineNumber="669"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This allows us to get efficient access to dominating loads or stores when</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00670" /><CodeLine lineNumber="670"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// we have a fully redundant load.  In addition to the most recent load, we</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00671" /><CodeLine lineNumber="671"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// keep track of a generation count of the read, which is compared against</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00672" /><CodeLine lineNumber="672"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the current generation count.  The current generation count is incremented</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00673" /><CodeLine lineNumber="673"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// after every possibly writing memory operation, which ensures that we only</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00674" /><CodeLine lineNumber="674"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// CSE loads with other loads that have no intervening store.  Ordering</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00675" /><CodeLine lineNumber="675"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// events (such as fences or atomic instructions) increment the generation</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00676" /><CodeLine lineNumber="676"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// count as well; essentially, we model these as writes to all possible</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="677"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// locations.  Note that atomic and/or volatile loads and stores can be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="678"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// present the table; it is the responsibility of the consumer to inspect</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="679"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the atomicity/volatility if needed.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="680" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/loadvalue"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">struct </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/loadvalue/#a20a42c6c09981e7a5e38494f3cfa1134">LoadValue</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="681" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/loadvalue/#a2ffa0c8239fbd7245a120f68750d58b1"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction">Instruction</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/loadvalue/#a2ffa0c8239fbd7245a120f68750d58b1">DefInst</a> = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">nullptr</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00810" /><CodeLine lineNumber="810"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Wrapper class to handle memory instructions, including loads,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00811" /><CodeLine lineNumber="811"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// stores and intrinsic loads and stores defined by the target.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00812" /><CodeLine lineNumber="812"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">ParseMemoryInst &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00814" /><CodeLine lineNumber="814"><Highlight kind="normal">    ParseMemoryInst(Instruction &#42;Inst, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> TargetTransformInfo &amp;<a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/#aa29b154aebb64d47175c1b82b04fd614">TTI</a>)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00815" /><CodeLine lineNumber="815"><Highlight kind="normal">      : Inst(Inst) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00816" /><CodeLine lineNumber="816"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (IntrinsicInst &#42;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvvmintrrange-cpp/#ac5804672fc0850438d63caec770647f8">II</a> = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a22eeee01734061ac1b31ccd994c49eef">dyn&#95;cast&lt;IntrinsicInst&gt;</a>(Inst)) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00817" /><CodeLine lineNumber="817"><Highlight kind="normal">        IntrID = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvvmintrrange-cpp/#ac5804672fc0850438d63caec770647f8">II</a>-&gt;getIntrinsicID();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00818" /><CodeLine lineNumber="818"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (<a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-earlycse-cpp-/earlycse/#aa29b154aebb64d47175c1b82b04fd614">TTI</a>.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targettransforminfo/#a02e4dcfc435f179592619b03330f643b">getTgtMemIntrinsic</a>(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvvmintrrange-cpp/#ac5804672fc0850438d63caec770647f8">II</a>, Info))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00819" /><CodeLine lineNumber="819"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00820" /><CodeLine lineNumber="820"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (isHandledNonTargetIntrinsic(IntrID)) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00821" /><CodeLine lineNumber="821"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">switch</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (IntrID) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00822" /><CodeLine lineNumber="822"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">case</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Intrinsic::masked&#95;load:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00823" /><CodeLine lineNumber="823"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.PtrVal = Inst-&gt;getOperand(0);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00824" /><CodeLine lineNumber="824"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.MatchingId = Intrinsic::masked&#95;load;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00825" /><CodeLine lineNumber="825"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.ReadMem = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">true</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00826" /><CodeLine lineNumber="826"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.WriteMem = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">false</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00827" /><CodeLine lineNumber="827"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.IsVolatile = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">false</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00828" /><CodeLine lineNumber="828"><Highlight kind="normal">            </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">break</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00829" /><CodeLine lineNumber="829"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">case</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Intrinsic::masked&#95;store:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00830" /><CodeLine lineNumber="830"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.PtrVal = Inst-&gt;getOperand(1);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00831" /><CodeLine lineNumber="831"><Highlight kind="normal">            </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Use the ID of masked load as the &quot;matching id&quot;. This will</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00832" /><CodeLine lineNumber="832"><Highlight kind="normal">            </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// prevent matching non-masked loads/stores with masked ones</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00833" /><CodeLine lineNumber="833"><Highlight kind="normal">            </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// (which could be done), but at the moment, the code here</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00834" /><CodeLine lineNumber="834"><Highlight kind="normal">            </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// does not support matching intrinsics with non-intrinsics,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00835" /><CodeLine lineNumber="835"><Highlight kind="normal">            </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// so keep the MatchingIds specific to masked instructions</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00836" /><CodeLine lineNumber="836"><Highlight kind="normal">            </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// for now (TODO).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00837" /><CodeLine lineNumber="837"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.MatchingId = Intrinsic::masked&#95;load;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00838" /><CodeLine lineNumber="838"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.ReadMem = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">false</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00839" /><CodeLine lineNumber="839"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.WriteMem = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">true</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00840" /><CodeLine lineNumber="840"><Highlight kind="normal">            Info.IsVolatile = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">false</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00841" /><CodeLine lineNumber="841"><Highlight kind="normal">            </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">break</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00842" /><CodeLine lineNumber="842"><Highlight kind="normal">          &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00844" /><CodeLine lineNumber="844"><Highlight kind="normal">      &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01872" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1872"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A simple and fast domtree-based CSE pass.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01873" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1873"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01874" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1874"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This pass does a simple depth-first walk over the dominator tree,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01875" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1875"><Highlight kind="comment">/// eliminating trivially redundant instructions and using instsimplify to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01876" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1876"><Highlight kind="comment">/// canonicalize things as it goes. It is intended to be fast and catch obvious</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01877" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1877"><Highlight kind="comment">/// cases so that instcombine and other passes are more effective. It is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01878" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1878"><Highlight kind="comment">/// expected that a later pass of GVN will catch the interesting/hard cases.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01879" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1879"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">&lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> UseMemorySSA&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
